1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Life admin arrives as screenshots, receipts, voice notes, PDFs, and tangled thoughts.
LifeInbox gives everything one calm, private place to land.

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Every account begins truly empty. There is no demo workspace:
each Appwrite record and file belongs only to the signed-in user.

3
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:30,000
One capture surface accepts text, images, PDFs, and voice.
I can organize actions or deliberately keep information as a permanent note.

4
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:40,000
This single thought contains three intentions: renew insurance, email Maya, and book a dentist.
I drop it in without organizing anything first.

5
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:50,000
GPT-5.6 Terra uses high reasoning and strict Structured Outputs
to separate every intent into three small, independent, source-grounded items.

6
00:00:50,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Each draft exposes its evidence, confidence, date, priority, and missing information.
I can edit or remove anything before a single item is saved.

7
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:10,000
After approval, all three items persist in Appwrite, survive a refresh,
and flow into Today and the Inbox without losing their source context.

8
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Smart Focus reduces the day to three clear moves and a quiet focus session.
Completed work stays searchable instead of disappearing.

9
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Not everything is a task. Notes preserve complete reference information until I delete it,
without polluting Today with fake outstanding work.

10
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:40,000
When information becomes actionable, I turn the note into a linked task.
Life Threads keep the action, people, dates, and original context together.

11
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:50,000
Ask LifeInbox reasons only over my permissioned workspace.
It recommends the next move, explains why, and returns citations instead of unsupported advice.

12
00:01:50,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Every citation opens its exact source item. LifeInbox Spotlight also finds
any task, note, person, or Thread without navigating through menus.

13
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:10,000
My data remains portable. LifeInbox exports a designed multipage PDF
with metrics, grouped items, notes, status, confidence, and page numbers.

14
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:20,000
The same clean workspace adapts to desktop, tablet, and phone, installs as a PWA,
keeps AI keys server-side, and supports complete deletion.

15
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Codex helped turn my product direction into tested architecture, resilient AI, and a deployed experience.
LifeInbox: drop it in, understand it, move on.
